<h2 id="version-034---alpha">Version 0.3.4 - Alpha</h2>
<ul>
  <li>Info: I don‚Äôt understand why some JS window/DOM-depended libraries exports their library to
      nodeJS using <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">module.exports</code>, so I‚Äôll just offer AMD only for the moment!</li>
  <li>Add: The options <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">csvOutput</code> and <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">csvSeparator</code> as well as a hidden CSV input method.</li>
  <li>Add: Support as Asynchronous Module Definition, tested with requireJS (I‚Äôm new with AMD).</li>
  <li>Update: The <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">animate</code> option is now set to <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">true</code> per default!</li>
  <li>Update: Correct use of the labels / placeholders.</li>
  <li>Update: The string-keys (+ the german translation).</li>
  <li>Bugfix: Escape RegExp Characters in Search string.</li>
